comment: broeder (this term is not used in normal speech, only in certain expressions, or with the meaning of "comrade")
zuster (this alternative for zus is probably not common in all regions in the Netherlands; but it can be used in certain expressions or to emphasize it)

maybe: oomzegger (not used in normal speech, but when explaining the relationship it can be used; about this term, I asked my brother and he said: never heard of); neefje (this is the term my brother would use)
